claim.claim-text:
1. A therapeutic pillow comprising:
a pillow with a trough therein, said trough extending linearly across a longest horizontal extent of a bottom side of said pillow; and
an insert, comprising a rounded surface corresponding to a shape of said trough, removably insertable into said trough;
wherein an area circumscribed by said trough and by an opening thereof is substantially in a shape of a semi-circular prism;
wherein a distance between a deepest point of said trough and said bottom side is substantially less than half of a distance between, and substantially more than a third of a distance between, a top side of said pillow and said bottom side.

2. The therapeutic pillow of claim 1, wherein said pillow is in a shape of a rounded rectangular prism;
wherein said top side and said bottom side are opposite each other and are largest sides of said rounded rectangular prism;
wherein a majority of said bottom side extends on a first side of said trough and a minority of said bottom side extends on a second side of said trough.

15. A therapeutic pillow kit comprising:
a pillow with a linear hollow in a shape of a prism therein;
a pillowcase with a sleeve in a location thereon corresponding to a location of said linear hollow; and
a plurality of inserts with shapes partially or wholly corresponding to said shape of said linear hollow;
wherein said sleeve is configured to accommodate each of said inserts;
wherein each said insert is removably insertable into each of said linear hollow and said sleeve.

16. The therapeutic pillow kit of claim 15, wherein each said insert comprises a ridged and/or smooth triangular and/or semi-circular prism;
wherein said insert comprises a first material and said pillow comprises a second material;
wherein a rigidity of said first material is greater than a rigidity of said second material.

20. The therapeutic pillow kit of claim 19, wherein said internal insert is made of a same and/or a different material as said insert;
wherein a same internal insert is usable for multiple said inserts;
wherein, when said insert is inserted within said trough, a portion of said pillow surrounding said insert is more rigid than a rest of said pillow.
